## Session start
1. Read `AGENT_MEMORY.md` fully.
2. Run `npm run agent:start` (or `node scripts/instruction-agent.js session-start`).
3. Fix memory drift before other work.

## After every prompt (before final response)
1. Update `AGENT_MEMORY.md` — append Session Update (never delete entries).
2. Run `npm run agent:end -- --summary "one line"`.
3. If MAJOR_CHANGES → `npm run agent:push`.

## Database trigger
If you touch `server/db/`, `server/services/`, ingestion, seeds, migrations, admin DB APIs, or `data/*.js`:
- Run `npm run agent:db-touch -- --actor "agent-name" --action "what you did"` immediately after.
- Document findings in AGENT_MEMORY.md.

## Major changes → auto-push GitHub
Push when 5+ files change, schema/migrations/tests/version change, or memory updated with new session.
